2 Case Study

Wealth and Life Expectancy (Gapminder)

Background

I learned a lot about ggplot the most during this assignment. It took me a while to understand the different aesthetics that were used to make the second graph. It is a great tool though for making good plots quickly.

Images

gap <- gapminder
gap <- filter(gap, country != "Kuwait", year == seq(1952, 2007, 5))
plot1 <- ggplot(gap, aes(x = lifeExp, y = gdpPercap, color = continent, size = (pop / 100000), group = country)) + 
  labs(x = "Life Expectancy", y = "GDP per Capita", size = "Population (100k)") +
  geom_jitter() +
  facet_grid(. ~ year) +
  theme_bw()
weighted <- filter(gapminder, country != "Kuwait", gdpPercap < 50000) %>% 
  group_by(year, continent) %>%
  mutate(av_mean = weighted.mean(gdpPercap, (pop / 100000)))
plot2 <- ggplot(gap, aes(x = year, y = gdpPercap)) + 
  geom_point(aes(color = continent, size = (pop / 100000))) +
  geom_line(aes(color = continent, group = country)) +
  geom_point(data = weighted, aes(x = year, y = av_mean, size = av_mean)) +
  geom_line(data = weighted, aes(x = year, y = av_mean)) +
  facet_grid(. ~ continent) +
  labs(x = "Year", y = "GDP per Capita", size = "Population (100k)") +
   scale_y_continuous(limits = c(0,50000)) +
  theme_bw()
